Czarna is a &lt;a href="village"&gt;village&lt;/a&gt; in the administrative district of &lt;a href="Gmina%20Serokomla"&gt;Gmina Serokomla&lt;/a&gt;, within &lt;a href="%C5%81uk%C3%B3w%20County"&gt;Łuków County&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="Lublin%20Voivodeship"&gt;Lublin Voivodeship&lt;/a&gt;, in eastern Poland. It lies approximately west of &lt;a href="Serokomla"&gt;Serokomla&lt;/a&gt;, south of &lt;a href="%C5%81uk%C3%B3w"&gt;Łuków&lt;/a&gt;, and north of the regional capital &lt;a href="Lublin"&gt;Lublin&lt;/a&gt;.
